### Story 2: Defining the Application Architecture
* **Details**: The application follows a modular, decoupled full-stack architecture.
  * **Frontend (Streamlit UI)**: Exposes a user-friendly layout with sidebar-based routing, handling user inputs and making HTTP requests to the backend ([app.py](file:///C:/Users/91767/networking-assistant/frontend/app.py)).
  * **Backend (FastAPI)**: Exposes REST API endpoints. Decouples business logic into a dedicated services layer ([main.py](file:///C:/Users/91767/networking-assistant/backend/main.py)).
  * **Database (SQLAlchemy + SQLite)**: Holds persistent suggestion and feedback logs ([models.py](file:///C:/Users/91767/networking-assistant/backend/models/models.py)).
  * **Services**: Encapsulates model executions ([nlp_service.py](file:///C:/Users/91767/networking-assistant/backend/services/nlp_service.py)) and external API integration ([wiki_service.py](file:///C:/Users/91767/networking-assistant/backend/services/wiki_service.py)).
